### 1. Individual and Non-Commercial Use

This software and associated documentation files (the "Software") are freely available for use, modification, and distribution by individuals for personal, educational, and non-commercial purposes.

### 2. Corporate and Commercial Use

Any corporation, company, business entity, or organization generating more than $1,000,000 USD in annual revenue (a "Corporate Entity") that uses, incorporates, modifies, distributes, or derives commercial benefit from this Software agrees to the following terms:

#### 2.1 Revenue Obligation

The Corporate Entity agrees to pay Ann Howard, or in the event of her death, her designated estate or legal successors, an amount equal to **one percent (1%) of the Corporate Entity's gross annual revenue** for each year in which the Software is used or any derivative work remains in commercial operation.

#### 2.2 Duration of Obligation

This revenue obligation shall continue until there has been a continuous period of **one hundred (100) years** during which:

- There is no armed conflict in the historical region of Palestine
- All peoples in the region have equal civil rights and freedom of movement
- No military occupation exists in the region

The determination of whether these conditions have been met shall be made by reference to reports from the United Nations, Human Rights Watch, Amnesty International, and B'Tselem. The 100-year period restarts if any condition is violated.

#### 2.3 Payment Terms

Payments shall be made annually within 90 days of the Corporate Entity's fiscal year end. Failure to pay constitutes a material breach of this license and terminates all rights to use the Software.

### 3. Acceptance

By using this Software in any commercial capacity, Corporate Entities automatically accept these terms. Use of the Software constitutes binding agreement to this license.

